---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout lang="en" title="Privacy" description="Privacy policy of First Up Productions — information on the processing of personal data under the GDPR.">

  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-black pt-32">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-10">Privacy</h1>

      <p class="text-sm text-brand-muted italic mb-10">
        This is an informational English translation. The legally binding version is the <a href="/datenschutz" class="underline hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors">German privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-brand-light/70 leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">1. Controller</h2>
          <p>
            Controller within the meaning of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is:
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Adem Kocyigit<br />
            First Up Productions (project / brand)<br />
            Tiefe Allee 33<br />
            24149 Kiel<br />
            Germany
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Email: <a href="mailto:firstupproductions.media@gmail.com" class="hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors">firstupproductions.media@gmail.com</a><br />
            Phone: <a href="tel:+491732118910" class="hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors">+49 173 2118910</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">2. Hosting</h2>
          <p>
            This website is hosted on <strong class="text-brand-light">Cloudflare Pages</strong> (Cloudflare, Inc., 101 Townsend St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). When the site is accessed, technically necessary connection data (e.g. IP address, user agent, date and time) are processed in order to deliver the content and to keep the service secure and stable. Legal basis is Art. 6 (1) lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in a secure and stable delivery of the website). Cloudflare may also process data in the USA; data protection is ensured via standard contractual clauses and the EU-US Data Privacy Framework.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Cloudflare privacy policy:
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors break-words">https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">3. Server logs</h2>
          <p>
            When the website is accessed, the hosting provider automatically logs technical data, including the anonymised or shortened IP address, date and time, browser type, referrer URL, and the amount of data transferred. This data is not combined with other data sources. Legal basis is Art. 6 (1) lit. f GDPR.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">4. Contact form</h2>
          <p>
            You can send inquiries through the contact form on this website. The following data is processed, insofar as you enter it into the form:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Name</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Email address</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Phone number, if provided</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Company / organisation, if provided</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Preferred timeline / deadline, if provided</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Budget range, if provided</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Content of the message</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Processing is for the sole purpose of handling your inquiry and any pre-contractual communication. Legal basis is Art. 6 (1) lit. b GDPR (initiation of a contractual relationship) and/or Art. 6 (1) lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in answering your inquiry).
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Form data is transmitted through <strong class="text-brand-light">Web3Forms</strong> (Onfra, Inc.). Web3Forms acts as a processor and forwards the data entered in the form as an email to my Gmail inbox. No persistent storage at Web3Forms takes place beyond this.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Web3Forms privacy notice:
            <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors break-words">https://web3forms.com/privacy-policy</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">5. Email communication (Gmail / Google)</h2>
          <p>
            Inquiries forwarded through the contact form, as well as emails sent directly to me, are received in a Gmail inbox operated by Google (Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland). Receiving and storing emails involves processing of technical connection and metadata by Google. Google may also process data in the USA; data protection is ensured via standard contractual clauses and the EU-US Data Privacy Framework.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If you contact me by email, your information is processed for the purpose of handling your inquiry and any follow-up communication. This data is not shared without your consent. Storage takes place for as long as needed to handle the inquiry; statutory retention obligations remain unaffected. Legal basis is Art. 6 (1) lit. b and/or lit. f GDPR.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Google privacy policy:
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors break-words">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">6. Cookies and tracking</h2>
          <p>
            This website currently uses no own tracking cookies and no analytics tools. Should cookies or comparable technologies that are not strictly necessary be added in the future, this will only happen with your explicit consent under § 25 (1) TDDDG in conjunction with Art. 6 (1) lit. a GDPR.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">7. External fonts</h2>
          <p>
            This website loads fonts from <strong class="text-brand-light">Google Fonts</strong> (Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland). When the fonts are loaded, your IP address is transmitted to Google. Legal basis is Art. 6 (1) lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in a consistent, professional appearance).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">8. Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            You have the right at any time to:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Access the personal data concerning you (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Have inaccurate data corrected (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Have your data deleted (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Restrict processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Object to processing (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-brand-accent mt-1">—</span> Lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To exercise your rights, you can contact me at any time using the contact details above.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-light mb-3">9. Status of this policy</h2>
          <p>
            As of: May 2026
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
